      "writtenOn": "2020-03-18T14:58:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "First a longer explanation of why there are different packages: I wanted to put each logging impl (glog, cloud logging, slog, etc.) in its own package to make the different options clearer. However, I also wanted to keep the current behavior where importing sklog means it works and logs to a default logger as soon as the program starts. The only way I can think of to do that is to have the sklog package depend on one of the impl packages. This implies that anything that the impl needs must not be in the sklog package to avoid a circular dependency.\n\nI think everything currently in sklog_impl needs to be in sklog_impl for this reason.\n\nWe could definitely redefine some things from sklog_impl in sklog. E.g.\nfunc SetLogger(l sklog_impl.Logger) { sklog_impl.SetLogger(l) }\ntype Severity \u003d sklog_impl.Severity\nconst Debug \u003d sklog_impl.Debug\n...\nI will let you follow up with a CL to do that if you wish.",
      "parentUuid": "097bb780_c9b91a18",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 127,
        "startChar": 21,
        "endLine": 127,
        "endChar": 40
      },
